node.title: Man Who Felt Called to 'Commit Sacrifices' Confessed to 5 Murders, Including Roommate's
node.description: On Monday, Jason Thornburg was indicted on a charge of capital murder for the deaths of three people found dismembered in a burning dumpster on Sept. 27.

node.title: Trump-Appointed Judge Trevor McFadden Strikes Down Ex-President's Suit to Hide Tax Returns
node.description: The judge leaned on past Supreme Court decisions to reject all of Trump's arguments, but Trump still has a way out.

node.title: Louisiana's John Bel Edwards Adds COVID Vaccine to School Requirements, Despite Objections
node.description: Edwards criticized "misleading and conspiratorial rhetoric" while announcing the COVID vaccine will be required in school for FDA approved ages, now 16 and up.

node.title: As David Warner faces a fitness test, here's everything you need to know ahead of the Adelaide clash
node.description: David Warner is facing a race against the clock to be fit for the Adelaide Test. Here's everything you need to know ahead of the first ball on Thursday.

node.title: NZ firm developing seaweed drink
node.description: AgriSea has been turning seaweed into fertilisers and animal health products for more than 25 years. Now it is turning its attention to a seaweed drink for people.

node.title: Olympian adamant NZ selection process needs to change
node.description: A long-time coach and three-time Olympian is calling what for what he describes as "favouritism" to be dropped from the selection process for national honours.

node.title: Alinghi confirm F1 partnership for America's Cup challenge

node.title: Boris Johnson's New COVID Restrictions Set Off Backlash From His Conservative Party
node.description: The new mandates were economically damaging and limited individual freedoms, argued many Conservatives legislators, with one calling them "a slippery slope."

node.title: Remains Found in Garbage Bag Almost 40 Years Ago Now Identified as Former O'Jays Guitarist
node.description: The remains found in Twinsburg, Ohio in 1982 were recently identified by local authorities as Frank Little, who had been missing for over 40 years.
